@page "/surfaces/button-groups"

<PageTitle>Button Groups</PageTitle>

<Container Padding="Padding.Is4.OnY">
<Row>
    <Column>
        <Div TextAlignment="TextAlignment.Center" Margin="Margin.Is5.FromEnd">
            <H1 DisplaySize="DisplaySize.Is4" FontWeight="FontWeight.Bold" TextColor="TextColor.Primary">Button Groups</H1>
            <Paragraph Class="lead" TextColor="TextColor.Muted">Group a series of buttons together on a single line or stack them in a vertical column.</Paragraph>
        </Div>
    </Column>
</Row>

<Row Gap="Gap.Is4">
    <Column>

        <Section>
            <H2>Basic Button Group</H2>
            <Paragraph>Wrap a series of buttons with a ButtonGroup component.</Paragraph>

            <ButtonGroup>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Left</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Middle</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Right</Button>
            </ButtonGroup>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Mixed Styles</H2>
            <Paragraph>Mix different button styles within a button group.</Paragraph>

            <ButtonGroup>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Primary</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Secondary">Secondary</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Success">Success</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Warning">Warning</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Danger">Danger</Button>
            </ButtonGroup>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Outline Buttons</H2>
            <Paragraph>Button group with outline style buttons.</Paragraph>

            <ButtonGroup>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary" Outline="true">Left</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary" Outline="true">Middle</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary" Outline="true">Right</Button>
            </ButtonGroup>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Vertical Button Group</H2>
            <Paragraph>Make a set of buttons appear vertically stacked rather than horizontally.</Paragraph>

            <ButtonGroup Vertical="true">
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
            </ButtonGroup>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Button Group Sizes</H2>
            <Paragraph>Instead of applying button sizing classes to every button in a group, just add the size class to the ButtonGroup.</Paragraph>

            <Div Margin="Margin.Is3.FromBottom">
                <H3>Small</H3>
                <ButtonGroup Size="Size.Small">
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Left</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Middle</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Right</Button>
                </ButtonGroup>
            </Div>

            <Div Margin="Margin.Is3.FromBottom">
                <H3>Default</H3>
                <ButtonGroup>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Left</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Middle</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Right</Button>
                </ButtonGroup>
            </Div>

            <Div Margin="Margin.Is3.FromBottom">
                <H3>Large</H3>
                <ButtonGroup Size="Size.Large">
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Left</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Middle</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Right</Button>
                </ButtonGroup>
            </Div>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Vertical Button Group Sizes</H2>
            <Paragraph>Vertical button groups with different sizes.</Paragraph>

            <Div Display="Display.Flex" Gap="Gap.Is3">
                <Div>
                    <H3>Small</H3>
                    <ButtonGroup Vertical="true" Size="Size.Small">
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                    </ButtonGroup>
                </Div>

                <Div>
                    <H3>Default</H3>
                    <ButtonGroup Vertical="true">
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                    </ButtonGroup>
                </Div>

                <Div>
                    <H3>Large</H3>
                    <ButtonGroup Vertical="true" Size="Size.Large">
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                        <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Button</Button>
                    </ButtonGroup>
                </Div>
            </Div>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Button Group with Icons</H2>
            <Paragraph>Button groups can contain buttons with icons.</Paragraph>

            <ButtonGroup>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">
                    <Icon Name="chevron-left"/>
                    Previous
                </Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">
                    <Icon Name="home"/>
                    Home
                </Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">
                    Next
                    <Icon Name="chevron-right"/>
                </Button>
            </ButtonGroup>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Button Group with Dropdown</H2>
            <Paragraph>Place a dropdown within a button group.</Paragraph>

            <ButtonGroup>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Action</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Another action</Button>
                <Dropdown>
                    <DropdownToggle BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">
                        Dropdown
                        <Icon Name="chevron-down"/>
                    </DropdownToggle>
                    <DropdownMenu>
                        <DropdownItem>Action</DropdownItem>
                        <DropdownItem>Another action</DropdownItem>
                        <DropdownDivider/>
                        <DropdownItem>Something else here</DropdownItem>
                    </DropdownMenu>
                </Dropdown>
            </ButtonGroup>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Button Toolbar</H2>
            <Paragraph>Combine sets of button groups into button toolbars for more complex components.</Paragraph>

            <Div Class="btn-toolbar" role="toolbar" aria-label="Toolbar with button groups">
                <ButtonGroup Margin="Margin.Is2.FromEnd" role="group" aria-label="First group">
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">1</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">2</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">3</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">4</Button>
                </ButtonGroup>
                <ButtonGroup Margin="Margin.Is2.FromEnd" role="group" aria-label="Second group">
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Secondary">5</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Secondary">6</Button>
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Secondary">7</Button>
                </ButtonGroup>
                <ButtonGroup role="group" aria-label="Third group">
                    <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Info">8</Button>
                </ButtonGroup>
            </Div>
        </Section>

        <Section>
            <H2>Accessibility</H2>
            <Paragraph>Button groups with proper ARIA labels and roles for accessibility.</Paragraph>

            <ButtonGroup Role="group" AriaLabel="Navigation buttons">
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Previous</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Primary">Next</Button>
            </ButtonGroup>

            <ButtonGroup Vertical="true" Role="group" AriaLabel="Vertical action buttons" Margin="Margin.Is3.FromTop">
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Success">Save</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Warning">Edit</Button>
                <Button BackgroundColor="BackgroundColor.Danger">Delete</Button>
            </ButtonGroup>
        </Section>
    </Column>
</Row>
</Container>
